	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have never gone through the lengths that you have to prove this, but my own experience with wis casters suggests that you are correct. Wisdom doen't seem to me to affect whether a spell "hits" for full damage. That is your opponent's resists. However, What wis does affect is fizzle rate. I have over 50wis in items, and rarely fizzle when I am fully equipped. However, when I am preparing for a corpse run, and have no equipment, I fizzle on common spells like buffs, and all my spell skills are at level max. The easiest way to see this is just to create a couple stacks of food. First make about 2 stacks fully equipped. Now strip all wis items and make 2 stacks. go back and count the fizzles.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
